\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\">Corporate governance is a system by which a company is directed and controlled. It&nbsp;is the backbone of a corporate entity</li><li class=\"\">It brings in a structure through which the organizational objectives of the company are set and are also pursued. It also sets the means of attaining those objectives; the strategic planning that might be necessary the financial planning as well as the&nbsp;operational planning&nbsp;</li><li class=\"\">The main actors in corporate governance are the shareholders and the investors as a class</li><li class=\"\">The agency problem is actually a conflict of interest in the relationship between two parties conflict of interest; two parties such that one of the party is supposed to act in the best interest of the other&nbsp;<br></li><li class=\"\">The major issue in corporate governance remains how to protect the investors' interest</li><li class=\"\">For better corporate governance, the top executive has to always be accountable</li><li class=\"\">Section 198 says that in the case of a public trading company the total managerial compensation must not exceed 11 per cent of the net profit the company makes that year. If it exceeds then government permission is required and it has to be discussed and disclosed in the general body meeting which is where the shareholders are</li><li class=\"\">Socially Responsible Investment (SRI) is a controlling tool used to send a message from the investors to the corporation</li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n"]}